<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Adkins v. Children's Hospital decision of 1923:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Established minimum wage laws</option>
            <option letter="b">Struck down women's minimum wage legislation</option>
            <option letter="c">Protected child labor</option>
            <option letter="d">Regulated hospital working conditions</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>In Adkins v. Children's Hospital, the Supreme Court struck down a minimum wage law for women workers in Washington D.C., ruling it unconstitutional under the Fifth Amendment's due process clause. The Court's decision reflected its pro-business stance and commitment to "freedom of contract," limiting government power to regulate working conditions and wages for women workers.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
